<subSubSection pageId="668" pageNumber="669" type="diversity">
<paragraph pageId="668" pageNumber="669">Diversity.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="668" pageNumber="669">About 45 species in the Nearctic (two species, one of them adventive), Neotropical (25 species), and Palaearctic (17 species) Regions.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="668" pageNumber="669" type="identification">
<paragraph pageId="668" pageNumber="669">Identification.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="668" pageNumber="669">
The two species found in North America have been covered by Lindroth (1968: 883-884, as 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="668" pageNumber="669">harpalinus</emphasis>
group).
</paragraph>
